
        
                READ ME 6/9/88


This collection of routines are the result of an internal Abraxas
project for developing a C PLUS PLUS (CPP) [C++] preprocessor and
compiler. We are distributing this code to assist the PCYACC user 
in developing new object oriented technology. We are active in many
OOPS projects.


The routines can be used as a starting point for a project using the
CPP language. In particular,the grammar specification includes all features
of CPP as given in the CPP reference manual. The following is a list of
relevant source files and their sizes:


---------------------------------------------------------------------

GRAM    Y       34776		// grammar specification

CPPCMAIN H        157		// header file for main program
GLOBAL   H      15382		// global types and variables
YYLEX    H         95		// header file for scanner
CONST    H       1322		// global constants
YYERR    H        164		// error header file

YYTAB    H       1865		// token definitions (generated from pcyacc)

YYTAB    C     113847		// parser program (generated from pcyacc)

LINK     C      20250		// parse tree construction routines
MAIN     C       3818		// main routine
AGGR     C      10472		// aggregate processing routines
TYPE     C      11488		// type (class) processing routines
LEX      C      11785		// scanner
FMT      C       6761		// resulting c code formatting
NEW      C      17086		// tree node allocation routines
GEN      C      20491		// c code generation routines
FCT      C      19071		// function processing routines
ERR      C        615		// error routines

MAKEFILE MAK     1038		// configuration management file

SOURCE   C       1000		// test result
SOURCE   LIS     1786		// source listing for test program
SOURCE   CPP     1306		// test program

---------------------------------------------------------------------

The executable program is built using Microsoft C Version 5.0 compiler,
with MEDIUM memory model. NOTE MICROSOFT C IS USED BECAUSE IT IS ONE
OF THE FEW C COMPILERS THAT CAN HANDLE A SWITCH STATEMENT WITH MORE
THAN 256 CASE DECLARATIONS.

* Note this grammar takes a long time to compile
